ce:section.ce:para:
The impact of nanomaterials on fibrillation are well-documented and the working mechanisms/assumptions are widely discussed. Here, we summarize possible mechanisms explaining how nanomaterials interfere, mainly by disrupting aggregation (Fig. 3
                      and Table 2
                     ). These data supporting these mechanisms are mostly based on in vitro studies due to grossly inadequate mechanistic studies in vivo.

Effects of nanomaterials on protein aggregation are closely dependent on the physical and chemical properties of nanomaterials, such as size, charge, surface roughness and surface modification. Here, we summarize the action mechanisms of several influencing factors (Table 3
                      and Fig. 4
                     ).
